Manchester United’s squad to face West Brom in the Premier League on Saturday night has been revealed. According to Manchester Evening News, Man United manager, Ole Gunnar Solskjaer, has released a full squad of 19 players to tackle West Brom at Old Trafford. Solskjaer had already confirmed at his pre-match press conference on Friday that the likes of Lingard, Phil Jones, Luke Shaw and Mason Greenwood will take no part in the West Brom clash. Solskjaer’s men head to the game following a 3-1 victory over Everton in their last Premier League clash before the international break. Man United’s full squad to face West Brom: David de Gea, Dean Henderson, Lee Grant, Aaron Wan-Bissaka, Victor Lindelof, Axel Tuanzebe, Harry Maguire, Alex Telles, Brandon Williams, Nemanja Matic, Donny van de Beek, Fred, Scott McTominay, Daniel James, Juan Mata, Bruno Fernandes, Marcus Rashford, Edinson Cavani, Anthony Martial. The kick-off time for the match is 9 pm.